<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12019a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12019a">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12019a"> 19(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Monte Gargano</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Aubert envoya des chanoines en Italie, au <mark>mont Gargano</mark>, le seul endroit o&ugrave; saint Michel e&ucirc;t d&eacute;j&agrave; un culte. <br><font color="green">[Aubert sent Canons to Italy, to the mount Gargano, the only place where saint Michael already had a cult.]</font> VI.C.15.bfr(e) <small> &Eacute;douard Schur&eacute;, <a name="ESLL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ESLL"><cite title="source">Les Grandes L&eacute;gendes de France</cite></a> (1892) 163</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: A mountain in Italy and the most famous sanctuary of St Michael when the Saint himself appeared to the Bishop of Avranches (see 15(l)) and demanded that a new sanctuary be erected, similar to <mark>Monte Gargano</mark>. </mm> </dd></dl>
